-- Samsung Electronics to upgrade chips
-- 
-- Mon May 28, 2007 11:47am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/05/28/us-samsung-investment-idUSSEO3639820070528

 

 SEOUL  (Reuters) - Samsung Electronics Co. Ltd. ( 005930.KS ), the world's biggest maker of memory chips, said on Monday it would invest 938.8 billion won ($1.01 billion) to upgrade its memory chip production lines. 

 The spending will be made during 2007 to refine its memory chip production process and boost productivity, Samsung said in a filing to the Korea Exchange. It did not provide other details. ($1=930.0 Won)